{
  "text": "Overall, the basic biochemical parameters of the six newly studied EctD enzymes and the re-analyzed EctD protein from V. salexigens [CITATION_1] were all quite similar (Table 1) , regardless of the environmental parameters that were prevalent in the habitats of those microorganisms from which they originate. However, differences were noted with respect to their resistance to the inhibiting action of increased salt concentrations (Table 1) .",
